   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary52.jpg"/>
            <head><date>Saturday 29</date>.</head>
            <p>We moved up today. We had been promised teams, but they didn't come, so we tugged
               away at a <objectName type="equipment">hand-cart</objectName> &amp; we were nearly
               done. Someone had raised a row over in town, and five 4 horse teams came in the
               afternoon, &amp; before evening we had all our luggage up. We have a motley
               collection of <objectName type="equipment">tents</objectName>, some of the 21st Mass,
               sibley, wall, common tents, great lumbering tents of the rebels. We managed to get
               two nice <objectName type="equipment">wall-tents</objectName> &amp; I pitched them at
               right angles - then we got part of a sibley &amp; made a portico in front - it looks
               [Swiss?] - one <persName key="Dick Coulter"
                  ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper025"
                  cert="medium">Dick</persName> has for his department. The other we eat &amp; sleep
               in. We have it all floored very nicely, &amp; tonight feel as if we were at home
               again. It seems like our canvas home at <placeName key="Annapolis, MD"
                  ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002"
                  >Annapolis</placeName>.</p>
         </div>
